<p align="left"><font FACE="Arial" size="4"><b>LEARN &quot;CAN DO&quot; LAW: MAKE A
DIFFERENCE</b></font></p>
<font size="1">

<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY"></font><font size="2">When an Alabama police officer could not find any
organization to teach about the special problems of school-based violence and crime, he
approached Law Advisory. I was only too happy to have our research staff take a look at
the area of law. </p>

<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">I discovered some disturbing facts. </p>

<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">Many school officials refused to cooperate with police, even in
dangerous situations, because they had been told that it would be illegal. Vice principals
believed this. So did principals. So did Superintendents and even some school attorneys.</font></p>
<font size="2">

<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">Even more frightening, some prosecutors were telling police to let
school officials do such potentially deadly searches as frisks for weapons <i>because the
case would be easier to win if the educator acted alone.</i> Clearly somebody had to do
something to aid the course of police-school relations.</p>

<p ALIGN="JUSTIFY">The somebody turned out to be YOU! You accepted the opportunity to step
forward and be counted as long as you had research like ours behind you. With <i>Law
Advisory&#146;s</i> help, you are making a difference in school safety. Thanks.</p>

<p ALIGN="right" style="margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px">Pat Holecek, President</p>
